data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a type of court with the authority to deal with a particular problem or disagreement

data.chText: 她把案件提交特别法庭审理。
data.enText: She took her case to a tribunal.

tr: an assembly (including one or more judges) to conduct judicial business

value.def: A tribunal is a special court or committee that is appointed to deal with particular problems.

example.ex: His case comes before an industrial tribunal in March.
example.tran: 他的讼案将于3月在劳资法庭受审。

example.ex: …when a tribunal finds that an employee has been unfairly dismissed.
example.tran: 当特别法庭裁定一名员工遭到不公平解雇时

value.tran: (审理特定案件的)特别法庭，审理委员会
